ad a blast Sunday in my first RvR battle.  Had to share it with others if you haven't tried it yet.  <br>
<br>
We all met at the border fortress at about 6pm (pst).  By then 2 other guilds/clans had sent their people to the border wall near the first Albion castle.  It takes about 20 min of running to get from the border fortress to the border wall.  The land is filled with powerful hostile critters so you have to stay awake *grin*.  <br>
<br>
By 6:30pm we are at the border wall.  The wall is secure so we move through to the field below the Albion castle.  There had to be about 40-50 of my fellow Hibernians in the field.  Our guild (Tuatha de Danaan) and another (Awnsleigh) seemed to be the two with the most people there.  The Albions rushed us and it was chaos with bodies everywhere.  Very hard to pick out an enemy target amongst the masses.  We pushed them back and then snippered them for a bit.  Then fell back to our wall across a small pass.  The Albions went on the offensive and attacked our wall.  The first attack was pushed back and they died in masses.  The second attack some foolish person on our side left the door through the wall opened and about 40 Albion knights rushed through (breached the wall).  Was a surprise to be in a central tower on the wall shooting down their wizards when a knight in shiny blue plate armor came in and slashed me up good.  Being a courageous ranger I err ran.  Only problem is when I jumped off our wall to land behind the wall there were about 10 enemy knights standing around me so I got skewered.  Funny thing is you cant see their names or guilds.  Just says Albion Invader, Saracen Invader, etc.  Nor can you hear what they are saying.  Just says someone speaks in a foriegn language.  The Albions look awesome with their full plate armor, billowing white cloaks, and the spell effects were amazing.  <br>
<br>
So then we /release and reform at our border fort while a few rangers that escaped hide in the woods near the wall and sniper the Albions.  <br>
<br>
By 8pm we return to the wall but find only 3-4 Albions defending it so they die in seconds and we have it again.  Then we charge through to the Albion castle.  This time it got boring since the NPC guards hit for like 700+pts (only have 200hp) so we can't take the castle and the Albions don't want to come out and play.  <br>
<br>
The highlight of my night came when a (yellow con) Saracen Scout snuck past me but I saw him and then he started moving through our troops.  I lined up a Crit shot and killed him with one shot.  Was great to see him appear dead in front of a bunch of our troops with me behind him with my bow drawn :-)<br>
<br>
Only made 19 realm points on my first raid but hope to see that grow soon.<br>
<br>
The battles are fast, wild and filled with confusion.  No exp lost when you die.  No taunting or rubbing it in since you can't see names or understand their talk.  Totally fun PvP experience.<br>
<br>
